You must be wondering... DO I NEED A SOCIAL MEDIA MANAGER (SMM) FOR MY BUSINESS? 🤔 ⁠
⁠
With everything shifting online, having a good social media presence for your business is more important now than ever. Here's why you need a Social Media Manager:⁠
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁠⁣⁠
⚡ It can save you time⁣⁠: ⁣⁠
Running a business isn't easy! When you have a million other tasks to do, having a Social Media Manager can help you take all those time-consuming tasks off of your plate, allowing you to focus on other aspects of your business.⁠
⁠
⁣⁣⚡ Boost Engagement:⁠
A SMM will create content that is meaningful and relevant to your audience. When your brand is well represented, you will definitely generate new leads.⁠
⁣⁣⁣⁠
⁣⁣⚡ Let’s you focus on the bigger things: ⁣⁠
It is okay to not enjoy every aspect of owning a business. You might want to concentrate on the bigger things and really dislike completing the mundane, day to day stuff like coming up with creative captions and captivating content for your social media platforms. A social media manager is generally very well versed in this particular type of task and can definitely take that off your hands and enjoy doing it! ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁠⁣⁠

Meet Dr Izz and the experiment he did today. 

Today was Izz’s last day of school with @playdatesg PD Adventurers programme. I still remember how a year ago, I struggled with the decision on whether to enrol him for this programme because it will mean having to inconvenient my dad to fetch him from school 3 days a week. 

We went ahead with the plan and for close to 3 months, dad dutifully fetched him from school.  In March, we ended up having to serve LOA, and Izz attended school for a few days only before #circuitbreakerSG happened.

When Izz’s school reopened in June, hubby and I took turns to send and fetch him from school and we no longer had to activate my dad. Amazing how things worked out by themselves and my biggest worry about having to inconvenient him became irrelevant, masya-Allah. 

Amidst all that, Izz has had such precious learning moments with @playdatesg , like this video of him here (even his brothers are curious about the experiment and are asking to try this at home!), I have no regrets signing him up for the programme. Here’s wishing @playdatesg all the best in the next phase of their journey and we can’t wait to see them make a comeback, much stronger and better than before! ❤️

🎥 by @playdatesg

Earlier this year and during circuit breaker, we were connecting and sharing how we navigated our own versions of lockdown. TLDR:  @sutajio is donating 10% of proceeds from each mask to @blessingsinabagasia for the month of October (just a few days left)! So click and shop for a good cause and wonderful craftsmanship!   Swipe ➡️ to see them 💛💛💛
  
About Sutajio:  It actually means studio in Japanese and they aim to design and produce well made lifestyle products.  It started with @juuyeow a self employed emcee/host who lost all event work due to Covid-19.  She started crafting and selling items to get by.   
  
Danli, is a producer who wears many hats and has experience in the fashion and creative field.  She brought the brand their first 20 customers!   
  
All products are proudly made in Singapore, handcrafted by 2 retired aunties and 10% for this month goes to @blessingsinabagasia!

text:
6 common myths of gum disease
.
1- Gum disease is not that common
.
On the contrary, gum disease is extremely common. .
2- don't have cavities so I can't have gum disease
.
Cavity-free doesn’t ensure you are in the clear where gum disease is concerned.
.
3- Having gum disease means I will lose my teeth
.
Not so! You don’t have to lose any of your teeth to gum disease if you practice good oral hygiene.
.
4- Bleeding gums during pregnancy is normal
.
While it’s true that some women develop a condition known as “pregnancy gingivitis,” it’s not true that everyone experiences this.
.
5- Bad breath can be an indicator of gum disease
.
Persistent bad breath or a bad taste in your mouth can be an indicator of gum disease and other oral diseases so it is important that you uncover what’s causing the problem.
.
6- I have diabetes and therefore I will also have gum disease.
.
If you have diabetes, you are at greater risk of developing some oral health problems, including gum disease, but it can be controlled so it's important that you are extra diligent with your oral health.
.
.
.

image_desc: Photo by M&B in Singapore. May be an image of coffee cup.
text:
What is best match for a slice of banana loaf to start your week? Ofcourse coffee! 😋🤤

Interesting fact: Do you know that coffee was discovered by a goat herder?
It was said that coffee was discovered by a goat herder in Ethiopia in the 1500s. He saw his goats eating coffee cherries. Afterwards, he observed a change in their behavior; they gained a high amount of energy and they didn’t sleep at night.  The herder shared his findings with local monks. After they made their own drink from coffee beans, they realized they could stay up all night and pray. Word spread to other Ethiopian monks and soon after reached all across the civilized world.

Photo by Muiee メイ on October 24, 2020. May be an image of one or more people.
text:
3カ月前に友人がシンガポール西部開発中のTengahで新築HDB応募を成功し、来月にはブロックとユニットの階を選ぶので(こんなに早いの⁉️😲) 今朝友人とToa PayohのHDB Hubに来て、新築HDB模型を見に来ました〜.
.
Tengahはシンガポール初グリーン計画とスマートシティの一体型で、ソーラーパネル設置は団地、エレベーター、照明など共用施設に提供、又雨水を貯めて区画内の植物への水やりに再利用するなど、車両は地下を通り、地上は徒歩と自転車で道路を渡るなど、緑に囲まれる”Forest Town” と名付け、新しいエコライフの団地エリア、全地域を完成するには2050年だそうです〜.
.
Photo 1 は Toa Payoh 僅かに残っているらせん階段があるHDB、モデルは友人😆.
.
皆さん良い日を❣️Stay Safe & Healthy 💪🏻
.
話說三个月前 友人成功申請了尚在开犮中的新加坡西部Tengah区的新組屋、沒想到下个月要选單位和楼层！
有这么快😲⁉️ 于是今早來到了Toa Payoh的HDB Hub來看看新組屋的模型～ .
.
Tengah 是新加坡政府打造的第一個全新的Forest Town, 其建设也将与周围的森林环境融为一体、Tengah也将被打造为智能市镇，如采用太陽能發電、智能照明系统与雨水采集系统节省水电，每个单位都将装置智能配电板和插座、以及提供智能家居设备、也是全岛第一個可以集中提供中央冷氣的组屋区、比传統的空调系統更节能源～ 另外也是首个“无车”市镇中心、釆用多层设计实现“人在地上走，汽车地下行”的概念，让居民能自在地步行或骑脚踏车穿行～
.
相當令人期待的綠化新镇呀！這庞大的工程予計2050年完成😳.
.
Photo 1 是Toa Payoh HDB Hub 后方有螺旋楼梯的旧组屋 
好像不久前完成上漆 友人客串模特😆.
.
㊗️大家 平安幸福！身体健康！Stay Safe 💪🏻.

image_desc: Photo by Peilin 👩🏻‍🎨 SG Storyteller 🇸🇬 on October 21, 2020. May be an image of 1 person and standing.
text:
When is NEGATIVE good news? When you've done the COVID-19 test 🦠⁠⠀
⁠⠀
What started as a slight sore throat grew into body and headaches, so I went to the neighbourhood clinic to get some lozenges 🤭 Answering 'YES' to the question 'do you have a temperature >37.9', running nose, sore throat, headache or nausea" was already strange, then the doctor told me it was MANDATORY that I go to the National Centre for Infectious Disease (NCID) for a swab test due to my symptoms 🏥⁠⠀
⁠⠀
I went to the NCID straight away and was assigned a seat. The doctors came over with laptops and machines on wheels (which they call 'cows' 🐄🛹😝) and asked me a lot of health questions to assess which tests I had to take, including a neurological test and x-ray ☠️⁠⠀
⁠⠀
And of course, the swab test.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
The swab is actually three parts: The long cotton swabs are poked down your throat and two nostrils 👃🏼 It's like having a pap smear done on your nose: Intrusive and very uncomfortable.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
The nurses had a cardboard basin on standby, as the throat swab hits your gag reflex 🤢 Thankfully, I didn't vomit but it made me tear and coughed very hard for a while. The good news? My activated runny nose made the nose swab less painful 😅⁠⠀
⁠⠀
👨🏽‍⚕️🩺👩🏻‍⚕️ Really, salute to the doctors, nurses and cleaners who keep us safe. Whilst COVID-19 can feel more distant for some of us, it is their reality every single day.⁠⠀
⁠⠀
So please, continue all the advisories of wearing your mask, not touching your face, sanitising and staying home when you can 😷⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Do you know anyone who has done the swab test? Tag them here so we can exchange swab stories! ⁠🙊
location: NCID National Centre for Infectional Diseases

image_desc: Photo by berrielilthings on October 21, 2020. May be an image of food.
text:
One of the most life-changing and hardest meals which I had to cook... not in terms of culinary finesse but emotionally... 

Life’s unexpected moments... back to when it was late May, my mum told me on Monday night that our almost 18.5yo dear fam doggo, @happieharrie was not feeling too good. I had a video call with him that night and he seemed alright. He even smiled at me. On the very next day - Tuesday, I was prepping ingredients for plans to cook mala hotpot for Wednesday’s dinner. Not too long later, I received news from my family that I would have to go back to bid farewell to Harrie boy as he was critically ill. I remember being very upset and threw these ingredients in the freezer in a frenzied and flustered flurry, along with keeping my sourdough starter in the fridge before we left. 

Two weeks after his passing, only then did I have the courage to look at these frozen ingredients (luckily, did not spoil 🤭) to start cooking and complete this dish. I am so glad I did as my family, especially my mum, enjoyed this homemade mala dish. 🥰🌶🥘🍛 Best part of this is adding as many ingredients and spice in the mix as you wish to. My sinful favs r absolutely tons of Taiwanese/Oriental sausage 🌭, luncheon meat 🥩, potato 🥔, enoki and shiitake mushrooms 🍄, along with the wonderfully textured beancurd skin and black fungus. Adding lotus root 🍠 will not hurt either. 🤤😋 It simply adds flavour to the pot of life. Appreciate the goodness that is present in your life. The present is a present 🎁 in all sense of the word. 

Taste note: to reduce sugar level for the next round as the HDL seasoning does not seem to be as intensely salty as before. 

Pictured here with leftover rice from @mrlorbak and egg drop spinach soup

image_desc: Photo by Muiee メイ on October 20, 2020. May be an image of one or more people and food.
text:
昨日久々に旦那氏と用事があり都会へ行きました、ランチは久々に琥珀で天丼を食べました〜うちの旦那氏は和食は日本で食べるのが美味しい主義で…シンガポールではあんまり食べに行かないんです…こちらの天丼は初めて食べて〜👍😋…でもやはり一番美味しい天丼は沖縄の海鮮食堂 太陽ティーダだって🙄 .... .
.
近くなのでMarina Bay Sandsへ寄りました、最近オープンした世界初「水上Apple Store」へ拝見しようが…予約制でWalk-inは出来なかったので残念…😓 外から建物の写真を撮りました〜その球体な未来的なデザインは非常にユニーク😲 夜になると球体の下部がさまざまな色のグラデーションに変化し、水の反射に合わせ一層美しく彩ってくれるようです〜次回は予約してからまた訪ねよう〜.
.
皆さん良い日を❣️Stay Safe & Healthy💪🏻.
.
昨天有事和老爷下城 
终于带了很阿宅的老爷来享用琥珀天丼
个人认为这家的天丼 可以㜩美在东京吃过的天丼
老爷有給👍 但他说心中认为好吃的天丼
依然是沖縄的 “海鲜食堂 太陽 ティーダ “ 🤣
今年无法出游 阿宅老爷 就请你將就一下啦～
顺便到附近的滨海湾酒店 看看新开幕不久 
苹果首家水上Apple Store~ 进入需要予约 无法Walk-in
只好到外面拍照 📷 看起来就像是漂浮在水面上的一个球体
白天 其周身的玻璃面板 反射着天空和周遭的景观
晚上 球体像个灯笼 下方会点亮呈现不同层次的颜色
下次要予约好才再访～.
.
㊗️大家 生活愉快！平安幸福 🙏.
.

image_desc: Photo by Muiee メイ on October 19, 2020. May be an image of food.
text:
友人から貰った自家製のNyonya Satay Sauce , 痛風で海鮮を食べれない旦那氏ですが、その代わりに普段食べている食材を使い、チキン.サテ.ピザ🍕を作りました🤣 サテソースはピーナッツバターと混ぜて、ピザに塗り残りはチキンと混ぜる、エシャロット、ピーマン、パインとチーズをピザにのせオーブンに入れ…🍕焼き上がり❣️チーズはサテの辛さを調節し、もっと美味くなりました❣️旦那氏も👍😋.
.
晩餐はインドネシア風のGado-Gadoにしました、サテソースにピーナッツバターと刻んだ落花生を混ぜて、温野菜にかけて出来上がり❣️ 意外にこのソースは温野菜、特にKeropok (えびせん)にも合う👍👍👍😋 .
.
久々に夕焼けが見えました〜皆さん良い日を❣️Stay Safe & healthy❣️.
.
友人送来的自家制 渔家娘惹沙爹酱、老爷因痛风 目前无法吃海鮮、就用在平日煮的食材里～做了Satay Chicken Pizza🍕 搭配了紅䓤、青椒、黃梨、芝士、雞胸肉
把沙爹醬混合 Peanut butter 凃一层在pizza 皮上方
剩下的混合雞胸肉 把食材都放在Pizza后  240度放进烤箱 8-10分鐘 即可！這Satay Chicken Pizza 真的很可以👍 芝士多少会把辣酸味中和 然而辣度变得剛好适合我們的味蕾 老爷大赞！👏👏.
.
晩餐弄了 印尼式的溫蔬菜沙拉 Gado Gado 🥗
可以把沙爹酱 混合Peanut butter + 花生碎+蜜糖 等
做為酱汁～ 昨天的晚餐試做了❗️調过的酱汁变得浓稠 伴蔬菜享用～ 真的很不錯👍 花生碎的口感和Peanut butter 把甜味提升 對不大吃辣的我们来說 味道恰好 😋 意外的这沙爹醬 沾虾餅吃也很搭 👍 .
.
今天难得见火烧云、好美 ㊗️大家 生活愉快！平安幸福 🙏.
.

image_desc: Photo by Muiee メイ on October 18, 2020. May be an image of food.
text:
一昨日友人から貰った自家製のNyonya Satay Sauce〜我が家ではサテソースを使うには少ないので、何を作るかなぁ〜瓶を開けて味見すると…アッ🤭ピーナッツ入りのBBQサテにディップするソースとは違うサテソース、懐かしい味でマレーシアの海鮮料理に使う赤いアサムカレーに近い味、辛いけど酸味と薄甘い味がして、香辛料やカレー葉っぱが沢山入れてるサテソースでした〜その味は何故かマレーシアで良く食べたIkan Bilis Bunの味にも似て…じゃあこのパンを作ろう❗️.
.
Ikan Bilisはマレー語ではにぼしの意味、そのパンは当地で辛味調味料サンバルと揚げたにぼしを入れてます〜サンバルの代わりにこのサテソースを使い、具はポテト、エシャロット、揚げたにぼしと砂糖を一緒に炒め.... Ikan Bilis パンが焼き上がり❣️旦那氏に試食してもらい…👍👍👍😋 自分も試して〜似ている👌 辛さも丁度良い❣️ポテトにも合う〜にぼしも美味しい❣️餡そのままでもご飯にめちゃ合う〜このパン又作ろう❣️.
.
皆さん良い週末を❣️Stay Safe & Healthy 💪🏻.
.
前天友人送来了 Homemade 的渔家娘惹沙爹酱 叫我试试～ 平日家里很少用沙爹酱 打开瓶子 尝了一口醤汁...唉？这味道 😮 ... 比較接近紅亞參咖哩 卻有著酸辣和㣲甜的滋味 
搭配海鮮料理最对味！比如 鱼、虾、苏东、虾婆、啦啦 等但是我家老爷因痛风 目前无法吃海鮮 ...😭 要做什麼好呢？
這味道也让我想起在马来西亚 常吃的Ikan Bilis Bun ～
好久沒吃了 不如动手做看看～ 
用这沙爹醬 取代Sambal 于马铃薯、红葱、小魚乾和糖
快炒一遍 做为馅料 ～ 尝一口...這醬汁配马鈴薯好搭喔 😋 
面包 烤出來後 請老爷試吃一口....👍👍👏👏 😋
味道真的很好 虽然不是用Sambal 但真的很可以👌
下次要再做Ikan Bilis Bun ❣️.
.
大家 生活愉快！平安幸福 🙏.
.

image_desc: Photo shared by Not a Tastemaker. on October 16, 2020 tagging @nikvoon, and @patricoantonio. May be an image of food.
text:
• W E ‘ R E  B A C K •

It’s been awhile since we last posted *apologies for the radio silence*. I haven’t been cooking as often as I would’ve liked to lately because sometimes it takes a lot out of me emotionally. This happens every once in awhile especially so when I miss my dad a lot. Sometimes, though, that’s the exact thing that brings me back into the kitchen, which brings me to this dish I made a couple of weeks ago.
.
.
.
My dad used to take my family to this Hakka style Yong Tau Foo (Niang Tou Fu) stall along Upper Thompson Rd. We’d never go without him because it’s a bit of a drive from our house. I try to do a little something in the kitchen on the 9th every month to honour him and I thought what better way than to try making it at home for @nikvoon and my mum for dinner. 
.
.
.
The yong tau foo items are pretty standard finds, but the key thing about this Hakka version is the sauce made with Taucheo (which I’ve developed quite an affinity for as of late) - a delicate balance between subtle sweetness that amplifies the natural saltiness of the Taucheo. Suffice to say it was a slam dunk this first attempt. Definitely doing this more often. 
.
.
.
Made by me, shot by him. 📷: @nikvoon

image_desc: Photo by Peilin 👩🏻‍🎨 SG Storyteller 🇸🇬 in Singapore with @joshfunkbooks, and @chalkandchakras.
text:
"Isn’t story-telling without face-to-face interactions much harder now?" 🤔⁠
⁠
IT IS! 😅⁠
⁠
Why? ⁠
⁠
Technical faults are my biggest nightmare! 🖥️😩🤯⁠
⁠
To combat this, I rehearse A LOT with different equipment, timing transitions and prepare different types of activities so the children can remain engaged through the screen 🎥👩🏻‍💻🤳🏽⁠
⁠
I miss seeing and hearing the children’s reactions and inputs to the stories SO MUCH! 😢 In face-to-face sessions, I watch and listen to their responses and adjust my sessions to make them more relevant and fun for them, which parents have said is one of my X-factors ✨⁠
⁠
So I super appreciate the parents who have film and send me their children’s enthusiastic responses and sent them to me 😍😘❤️⁠
⁠
To see some of these adorable reactions, go to my 'Storytime' IG Highlights 🤩⁠
⁠
💫 For more of such Q&A, read my interview with @ChalkandChakras , which is linked in my bio!⁠

image_desc: Photo shared by RUTH 🙃🇸🇬 on October 12, 2020 tagging @pemconfinementnanny. May be an image of 3 people and people standing.
text:
Where did time go?! #throwback to the first month of bb Gen’s life, when I struggled with post partum recovery, crazy hormones and the massive change of role in the midst of #covid_19 #circuitbreakersg. 

From the nursing schedule to the changing of diapers to the bathing, dealing with regurgitation, even labeling of milk bags etc, Aunty Xueling emptied her bag of motherhood tips and tricks to make me less of a noob. I’ve adopted some of her good habits and am still using them till date. 

I’m so glad that our paths crossed through @pemconfinementnanny and I can’t recommend her enough. Aunty Xueling was truly the calm to my nerves back then. I still can recall (very vividly 😆!) myself screaming “Auntyyyyy!!!” when bb Gen merlion-ed her entire milk intake for the first time and we froze, not knowing what’s happening or what to do. 😅

If there is just one tip to share, it is to shadow your nanny in the final week of the confinement period and try everything yourself while she watches over you. We did this and definitely felt more equipped caring for bb Gen afterwards. 

PS: Aunty Xueling’s number is 999 if you’re looking specifically to book her for your confinement. 😊

There are only three ingredients in this deliciously fruity Apple crème recipe, can you make a guess how many apples you’ll need for this recipe? 🤔 Watch on to find out!⁠
⁠
𝐈𝐍𝐆𝐑𝐄𝐃𝐈𝐄𝐍𝐓𝐒⁠
4 tbsp @schar_glutenfree_sg Mix C - Mix Pâtisserie⁠
4 apples⁠
2 tbsp sugar⁠
⁠
𝐏𝐑𝐄𝐏𝐀𝐑𝐀𝐓𝐈𝐎𝐍⁠
1. Peel and dice the apples, place in a casserole, and add sugar.⁠
2. Cook until the apples begin to break up.⁠
3. Then turn the heat to low and mash the apples with a fork.⁠
4. Add flour and stir briskly with the fork until the mixture thickens.⁠
5. Allow the crème to cool.⁠
6. Serve in custard cups or use as a cake crème.⁠

image_desc: Photo by Samantha on October 11, 2020. May be an image of 1 person and standing.
text:
Been wanting to talk about this for a while but never found the chance so... since today marked my 100th @webarre class, I guess today is as good as any!

If you follow my stories these days, you would see that I post about fitness A LOT. The truth is - I’m actually very new to this fitness community and I’m actually amazed at how much my life has changed in the last 10 months.

I went for my very first studio class on 24th December 2019. I remember going alone to a Meltdown class at Haus and looking very out of place in my free running tee shirt and FBT shorts (whilst everyone was in their nice activewear 🤣) and finding the class ridiculously hard.

You see, fitness has always been an “on-off” part of my life, partly due to circumstance and partly due to a short attention span. I was in dance all my life (from age 3 all the way to university) but stopped dancing when I started working in London. I picked up gymming because we had a beautiful gym in our office in Canary Wharf but stopped when I injured myself flying off a treadmill (yes, I did, I went down in history in CC london for this embarrassing incident). I didn’t pick up fitness again until late 2017 when I became obsessed with running for 4 months (which resulted in 8 races completed, 2 of which were half marathons!) but then stopped soon after because work got hectic and wedding planning came into the picture. Before I knew it, two years had flown by and my trainers were just collecting dust at home.

Something “clicked” during my studio class on 24th December 2019 though. I had just resigned from my private practice job and was about to embark on a 9-week funemployment break before my new job starts in March. Most people take funemployment as a chance to travel the world but I was determined to “do something that is good for me”, especially after 2 years of long hours, stressful days and neglecting my physical and mental health. Despite my very “fish-out-of-water” first class, I loved it and subsequently booked my next class on 28th December (spin at Absolute!) and my third class on 3 January (barre at Webarre!). I was hooked and the rest was history.

(contd...)

image_desc: Photo shared by Innobake on October 09, 2020 tagging @baking_taitai. May be an image of text that says 'C © Baking Taitai baking_taitai'.
text:
Repost @baking_taitai 
Anybody craving some hot cross buns? 🥵
Made with 𝐁𝐥𝐮𝐞 𝐉𝐚𝐜𝐤𝐞𝐭 𝐁𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐝 𝐅𝐥𝐨𝐮𝐫 - Click the link in bio to view our full range!
.
Be sure to visit @baking_taitai  for more!
• • • • • •
Here’s sharing my Hot Cross Buns recipe which I have tweaked from my favorite wholemeal butter buns recipe and it’s so soft and fluffy!
.
.
[👩🏻‍🍳𝐁𝐚𝐤𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐓𝐚𝐢𝐭𝐚𝐢’𝐬 𝐇𝐨𝐭 𝐂𝐫𝐨𝐬𝐬 𝐁𝐮𝐧𝐬 𝐑𝐞𝐜𝐢𝐩𝐞]
.
𝗜𝗻𝗴𝗿𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗕𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗱 𝗗𝗼𝘂𝗴𝗵:
315g 𝐁𝐥𝐮𝐞 𝐉𝐚𝐜𝐤𝐞𝐭 𝐁𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐝 𝐅𝐥𝐨𝐮𝐫
160ml fresh milk 
1 egg
1/8 tsp salt
40g sugar
1 tsp ground cinnamon 
3g instant dry yeast
45g unsalted butter
50g dried raisins
50g dried citrus peel
.
𝗙𝗹𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗣𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗲 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗣𝗶𝗽𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗖𝗿𝗼𝘀𝘀𝗲𝘀:
3 tbsp 𝐁𝐥𝐮𝐞 𝐉𝐚𝐜𝐤𝐞𝐭 𝐀𝐥𝐥-𝐏𝐮𝐫𝐩𝐨𝐬𝐞 𝐅𝐥𝐨𝐮𝐫
1 tsp caster sugar
2.5 tbsp water
.
𝗚𝗹𝗮𝘇𝗲:
2 tbsp marmalade jam
2 tsp water
.
.
𝗠𝗲𝘁𝗵𝗼𝗱:
1. Mix all the ingredients (except butter and dried fruits) till everything is combined. Add in the dried fruits, continue to knead until dried fruits are well mixed into the dough. Then add in the butter and knead till window pane stage. Proof for an hour or until dough doubled in size.
.
2. Punch dough to release air then divide into 12 portions.
.
3. Roll round and placed the dough onto a baking pan laid with baking paper. Cover with a damp cloth and proof for about 60 minutes or until 1.5 times bigger.
.
4. Pipe crosses on proofed bread dough.
.
5. Bake in a preheated oven 200°C top/bottom heat for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
.
6. After baked, brush the top with glaze. Serve warm.
.
.
.

image_desc: Photo by Muiee メイ on October 09, 2020. May be an image of food.
text:
毎年の年末は海外で過ごすのが定番で、今年はシンガポール😭... その話しをしていると、突然旦那氏が”あの甘い卵焼きシンガポールにも売っているかなぁ” 〜アッ…伊達巻きの事か…😑 2年前の年始年末は東京で過ごし、初めて伊達巻を食べた旦那氏は大喜び❤️ そんなに食べたいんだ…ネットで調べたら意外に簡単〜でもハンペンは近くで買えないので、ローカルの魚漿を代用に〜初めて作る伊達巻き、ちょと上手く巻けない😑 味は似ているが…魚漿の味が少し重い、次回作るに少し減らそうかなぁ…旦那氏は👍でも少しFishy🐟って🤣 ドンキーで買ったキンキの一夜干し、美味しかった👍ホッケも買ったので、楽しみ❣️.
.
皆さん良い日を❣️Stay Safe & Healthy 💪🏻.
.
和老爷聊到年末、本应今年未将在沖縄渡过 
奈何今年因疫情无法成行 谈话中聊到2年前在东京跨年
突然”那甜味的蛋卷 新加坡有卖吗？” 
他说的甜蛋卷是伊達巻き(Date-Maki) 
日本正月的御節料理中不可缺的伊達巻き
年未时期各大超市都可以买到 給老爷吃後
他立即喜歡上了这帶甜味的蛋卷
在日本是用ハンペン(日式魚饼)比較不Fishy
但是附近的Donki 沒卖 只好用魚漿代替
加入鸡蛋、味醂、料理酒、砂糖 用攪拌器打均後
用小火慢慢煎 用竹簾巻起 冷藏4小時定型  伊達卷就完成✅
老爷吃一口👍 “但是有一點Fishy “ 🤣  味道还是可以的～
在Donki 买了Kinki 魚的一夜干、很好味😋 
也买了北海道的𩸽鱼(Hokke Fish) 期待中～.
.
㊗️大家 周末愉快 平安幸福！.
.

🍼Bao Makers🍼 

Salmon Mentai Don $12.90 
Beef Sliced Don $14.90
Charcoal Chicken Bao $3.30 

Love the minimalistic and chic interior, went on a slow Monday and this cafe/ restaurant was already bustling with hungry patrons by 1pm! 

What’s Bao Makers without their Baos right???? Taking normal baos up a notch, their perfectly crisp charcoaled chicken with their specialty sauce complemented the sesame bun perfectly. Soft and tender with the crisp from the chicken. Mmmmm. 

Salmon Mentai was generous with their mentaiko sauce and was so filling ! Super yummy from this “small bowl” and definitely filled me up for the rest of the day. 

Overall damage (2pax) ~ $30

.
他の国(日本、フランス、オーストラリア、サンフランシスコ、ロンドン、香港マカオなど)バージョンも出版され、旅の思い出に良いお土産でお勧めです❣️.
.
皆さん良い日を❣️Stay Safe & Healthy 💪🏻.
.
Facebook 的回忆顯示 5年前的今天在紐約🗽 犹记当时本应在6月出发、奈何四月动了大手术、延迟至10月才出犮前往纽约. 突然想起了这本在纽约图书馆附属的书店内购买的panorama pops、还有影片中的cubebot, 拿出来玩玩和翻阅...居遊的三星期 分别住宿在华尔街、Chelsea和Upper East, 不赶景点 漫遊纽约 留下了不少美好的回忆❣️

这系列的panorama pops 也有其他国家版本、如日本、法国、英国、香港澳门、澳洲等、价格约美金$10左右、是件很不錯 滿值得收藏的纪念品、相当推荐👍.
.
㊗️大家 工作愉快 平安幸福！.

[JUMP ROPE] I’ve always been an active individual. I exercise almost every day. It is a form of stress relief for me. I particularly like to run as I can clear my thoughts and think through matters when I run.
.
.
.
On 7 April 2020, Singapore started its lock down (we call it circuit breaker, aka CB). There was restrictions on movement and also social activities. Even though Singaporeans are permitted to run outside, I still try to minimise running outdoors. I started to do more indoor workouts. During this period of time, I also started to jump rope.
.
.
.
The fact is, I am not unfamiliar with jumping rope. I used to jump rope every now and then. I love the fact that it is a good cardio exercise that makes me really sweat. The first video here is taken in 7 Jan 2020. Notice my poor form with my arms outstretched and my high knees when doing "double unders”.
.
.
.
On 18 April 2020, I decided that I want to pick up jumping rope seriously. Since then, every single day, I make it a point to jump rope. The second video here is taken on 25 April 2020, one week after the start of my jump rope journey.
.
.
.
Fast forward to now (6 months later), I am still jumping rope daily. I’ve picked up a lot more tricks, and my form and speed has improved. The jump rope community on Instagram is amazing and I’ve certainly learnt a lot from many talented individuals in the community. The third video here is taken on 5 Oct 2020. Don’t think I will be stopping this amazing exercise soon! 💪🏻 Glad that I found a new passion 😁

text:
@49seats aims to satisfy customers’ tastebuds with their variety of fusion western cuisine 🍴

The pasta came piquant and tantalizing with a good combination of savoury and spicy elements, derived from salted egg and tom yum. The mussels and prawns were fresh while the chicken was crispy, pairing well with the accompanying creamy sauce.

Round up your meal with the Rainbow Fantasy Cake w Ice-Cream, a dessert filled with many colours, including the crispy flakes, decadent rainbow cake filled with luscious cream within, and the accompanying 3 scoops of ice-cream for maximum indulgence 🍨

image_desc: Photo by growBEyond on October 05, 2020. May be an image of 3 people, hair and people standing.
text:
A talented tween-ager!

Elliana Patel is 12 years-old and attends UWC East.  She has always been interested in social justice issues, particularly around gender and racial inequality.  Elliana is a pretty spectacular child for a few reasons but here are some of her accomplishments:

#AmbassadorForADay
Last year, she won the Expat Living’s ’Ambassador for a Day’ contest where she was one of the girls chosen to spend a day with a female ambassador in Singapore and was featured by both, Expat Living and the U.S. Embassy, Singapore.

#SlimeTime at 10!
When Elliana was just 10 years old - she launched her business “SlimeTime by Elliana” where she was a party entertainer making slime at children’s birthday parties. She observed keenly as to what the kids enjoyed and made efforts to improve her business and made her first earnings as well.

#CommunityService
Elliana’s family strongly believes in giving back. “As a family activity, we volunteer together at Willing Hearts. We also try and build in a service component on our holidays. On our last vacation to Turkey, we worked with a local NGO delivering meals to Syrian refugees in Istanbul,” adds the enterprising tween.

#ClimbEveryMountain
Elliana thought of a unique way of adding adventure and staying fit during over circuit breaker. Her entire family committed to climb to the height of Mt Everest (8,848m) using their condo’s stairwell!  Elliana ’summited’ under 30 days by climbing 28 floors 89 times! Stay at home certainly was dynamic for this family.

Thank you @nehafpatel for sharing this with us.

If you know of any kids with an inspiring story or a special talent, please email us at info@growbeyondsg.com.

text:
牛乳がかなり残っていて賞味期限前に使わないと〜思ったのがプリン🍮🤣日本ではいつでも気楽にコンビニやスーパーで買えるプリンが、シンガポールではめちゃ難しい…😑 久々に作りました〜美味しい❣️ロックダウン時期に中々コチュジャンが買えなくて、やっと先日Korean Storeで好みのコチュジャンが買えました❣️久々にビビンバと焼肉にしました〜近くのドンキーには何故か沢庵と稲荷が売って無いので韓国のを買い~ ん…個人的に沢庵の味は韓国より日本のがもっと好み🤣. スーパーから買ったサツマイモを蒸して食べたら…すじが多くて食べにくい😑 どうしよう〜っと思ったのが大学芋風に👍❗️🍠 美味しく出来上がり、しかも完食しました🤣.
.
皆さん 良い日を❣️Stay Safe & Healthy❣️
.
还有剩余的牛奶 
在没过期前赶快做成 custard pudding 🍮
食蒸好暖暖的布丁 真的很棒 👏😋.
.

終於在West Mall的韩国店舖
买到这品牌(加醋調好味)的Gochujang

久違的做了伴饭和煎烤Pork Belly 沾Gochujang配生菜 😋
.
超市买了越南產的日本番薯🍠
蒸好后 試吃一个口....有不少筋絲 口感不很好
再試一个 ...也是有 😑 怎办好呢……
想起不如做成日式的大学芋(Daigaku-imo)❣️
這是一道有咸甜味的煎番薯  好滋味 很快吃掉一半了🤣
.
也顺便做了在沖縄吃过的コンビーフハッシュ(Corned Beef  Hush - 把Corned Beef 和hushbrown 放在一起煎炒的美式料理）午餐就搭配面包、雞蛋和沙拉菜 享用吧！

We are so excited about this collaboration with Nikoi Island. We are not stopping adults from signing up. Because.

What to expect:
1) In this edition of Clean Days X Fawn Labs, the children will receive all ingredients and equipment to make 2 toxin free products. 2 Bath Bombs and a Body Wash 350ml. Keep the kit to make your own Bath Bombs from home.

We collect used containers post event to sterilise and reuse. Instructions will be given with the kit.

2) Parents can join in a session at the end of this virtual event to learn to read ingredient lists on Kids store bought bath time products as well as identify potential toxins. Our certified Organic Skincare Formulator will help you decipher the ingredient lists on some of your kids bath time products.

3) We will explore Sustainability, Eco Tourism, Environmental Conservation topics in a fun way for the kids. 

4) A HUGE giveaway for all participants: 
- a discount code for all future workshops at Fawn Labs. 
- a special gift from Nikoi Island, so that you can enjoy your next island visit for longer with compliments from Nikoi Island.

❣AN UPDATE ON MYSELF❣

Well, finally im in my 70s, yes, there's alot of ups and downs during the process but i keep my mindset strong. My mindset is stronger than before as ive tasted the small acheivement and now im craving for more better results. 

Its true, you wont always be motivated, there are days you feel like giving up, do not stop, just take a short break and be present, remind yourself why you started in the 1st place. 

In the beginning, i was "oh man i need to lose 45 kg in order to achieve my ideal weight? That's alot" Yet here i am, lost 20 kg and 25 kg more to go! 
Ill try my very best to get my ideal weight by the end of year. 

Most of my pants doesnt fit me anymore and i have to pin them / sew them (anyhow) 😅. Basically my waist is getting smaller but my hips ... not so much! I know what i have to do. 

How about you? 

I am thankful for my team, having coachee under me is a motivation, seeing them putting in so much effort and wanting the best, makes me motivated to do better to be a great example for them 🥰

text:
🌻Happiness is a journey where nothing goes wrong. The connection is simple. And someone is waiting for you. Smiling. 🌻Happiness is McDonalds breakfast and pancake drawing on a Friday! 😍 Spent some time bonding with my 2-year old younger nephew yesterday and he’s no longer a baby though I always struggle to understand his baby language. 🤣 So, yesterday he was trying to ask me to draw “...bus” for him. Yet he frowned when I drew a bus.. then he started singing..PJ Masks~~~ PJ Masks~~~ 🤣🤣🤣 He was so happy when I drew his PJ Masks! So today 姑姑 draw another PJ Masks for you again! ❤️I think most mummies with boys are familiar with PJ Masks. 🤪Quite cute little Superheroes and I finally realised their differences today (apart from the colours). 😅  TGIF and hope we all have positive superheroes power like PJ Masks to carry over the weekend! 💪💪💪🌻🌻🌻

image_desc: Photo by Muiee メイ on October 01, 2020. May be an image of one or more people, sky and buildings.
text:
IKEA Alexandraで友人と買い物した後、近くのQueenstownエリアので有名なDawson SkyTerraceとSkyVilleの団地を拝見に来ました〜
Queenstownは都会に近いけど、その辺りのHDBは古くて、お年寄りが住む古い町と認識されてますが、ここ近年では古いHDBが順次建て直しされ、Condoも多く立ち、IKEA、ホテルやモールなどオープンされ、また近代的で洒落た新しいコンセプトのHDB景観も加わりました〜その代表がSky Terrace@DawsonとSky Ville@Dowson👍 チャイナタウンのThe Pinnacle@Duxtonと同じくスカイガーデンがある団地です❗️写真はSky Ville@Dawson, Sky Terrace@Dawsonのすぐ隣り、建物はチャイナタウンのThe Pinnacle@Duxtonと似たような同じ設計でした❗️ちなみどちらも屋上は共有のテラスで、住民でなくても出入り自由❣️特にSkyVille@Dawsonの屋上は見晴らしが良くてお勧めです〜.
.
この辺りにまだ沢山の英植民時代Black & White Houses(プール付き)が有るとは 凄いですね〜もちろん値段も普通のHDBより高い、丁度5年MOP(Minimum Occupation Period) 満期で転売許可、property guruでSkyVilleの転売価格を見ると…同じくコンド並みの値段です😱.
.
前陣子和友人到IKEA Alexander 购买东西后 来到近处 Queenstown的Dawson区来看获得设计奖最高荣誉的政府组屋. 这里分享的是Sky Ville@Dawson、就在Sky Terrace@Dawson 的隔壁、其外观设计 咋看一眼 有像牛车水的The Pinnacle@Duxton (新加坡首个超过50层楼高的政府组屋). 和The Pinnacle@Duxton 一样、 Sky Ville@Dawson 也设有Roof Top Garden (47 Floor)、不过这里不收费(Sky Terrace 也是) 从这里可以360度 眺望Queenstown, Commonwealth 周边的景色, 沒想到周围还保留了不少英植民建筑(有游泳池）、也可以见到Sentosa, Labrador Park和Pasir Panjang Terminal. 看了网上的设计图、Sky Ville由12栋组层於菱形排列並通过空中花园连接成型、除了47楼分别在3,14,25,36楼也有Sky Garden 连接每栋楼～也刚好MOP5年 看了一下 转售屋价... 😲 价格一样可㜩美私人公寓呀！👍
.
㊗️大家 平安幸福！身体健康！Stay Safe 💪🏻.
